tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  26,160,"The people of Lut disbelieved in all the messengers by their rejection of Lut (peace be upon him)."
  26,163,"“So be mindful of Allah by fulfilling His commandments and refrain from that which He has prohibited. And obey me in whatever I command you with and forbid you from.”"
  26,165,"“Do you seek sexual gratification from males?”"
  26,166,"“Whilst neglecting sexual gratification from the front passages of your wives Allah has created for you? You have indeed transgressed the limits of Allah by this detestable absurdity.”"
  26,170,"So I accepted his supplication and saved him and his whole family."
  26,176,"The people of the Thicket close to Madyan rejected the Messengers when they rejected their prophet Shu‘ayb (peace be upon him)."
  26,179,"“So be mindful of Allah by fulfilling His commandments and refrain from that which He has prohibited. And obey me in whatever I have commanded you with and forbidden you from.”"
  26,183,"“And do not violate the rights of people and cause excessive corruption on Earth by committing sins.”"